					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Usually, JMP (xxxx) is done with an address in RAM.  When you defined your address, you probably have a general idea of where your variables are.  Yes, it screws up if xxxx and xxxx+1 are on a different page, but I usually stick both bytes in the zeropage anyway.
<br />I can't think of many situations where you'd want a 16-bit address sitting in ROM, and using a JMP (xxxx) to go there indirectly.
<br />
<br />Conveyor belts are usually animated with palette animation, but I didn't play Double Dragon 2, so don't know how the game animated them.</div>

					
